text: Coral Keys is an album led by pianist Walter Bishop Jr. which was recorded in 1971 and originally released on the Black Jazz label.Walter Bishop Jr. catalog accessed April 20, 2017Black Jazz LP discography accessed April 20, 2017Black Jazz Records Catalog accessed April 20, 2017 == Track listing == All compositions by Walter Bishop Jr. # "Coral Keys" – 5:44 # "Waltz for Zweetie" – 5:22 # "Track Down" – 6:30 # "Soul Turn Around" – 5:31 # "Our November" – 5:15 # "Three Loves" – 4:44 # "Freedom Suite" – 9:33 == Personnel == *Walter Bishop Jr. – piano *Woody Shaw – trumpet (tracks 5–7) *Harold Vick – flute, soprano saxophone, tenor saxophone *Reggie Johnson – bass *Alan Schwartz Benger (tracks 5–7), Idris Muhammad (tracks 1–4) – drums == References == Category:Walter Bishop Jr. albums Category:1971 albums Category:Black Jazz Records albums
